text.tspan: Active Manifold Exploration
DM Losey*, Y Chen*, S Huang*

tspan.tspan: Summary
: We develop a novel dimensionality reduction method that combines Hessian local linear
embedding and a modified form of active learning
to allow for the estimation of a nonlinear manifold in a
noisy environment. Our algorithm identifies important regions in the domain where additional sampling is

text.tspan: needed and actively updates the manifold estimation based on these new queries.

How learning unfolds in the brain: toward an optimization view
JA Hennig, ER Oby, DM Losey, AP Batista*, BM Yu*, SM Chase*
Neuron (2021)

tspan.tspan: Summary
: Is learning in the brain different from learning in artificial neural networks? We
highlight three key features that we observe in the brain that are not properties typically
considered when training artificial neural networks. (1) Neural variability is largely inflexible
during learning, (2) multiple learning processes are often at play and (3) there are often large
task-nonspecific changes.

text.tspan: BrainNet: a multi-person brain-to-brain interface for direct
collaboration between brains
L Jiang, A Stocco, DM Losey, ... , RPN Rao
Scientific Reports (2019)

tspan.tspan: Summary
: BrainNet is a noninvasive brain-to-brain interface that allows collaboration
between several users by only the modulation of neural activity. The intention of one user is
decoded from their neural EEG signal. This intention is encoded in the neural stimulation of
another user, who can then respond by modulating their own neural signals.

text.tspan: Playing 20 questions with the mind: collaborative problem
solving by humans using a brain-to-brain interface
A Stocco, CS Prat, DM Losey, ... , RPN Rao
Plos One (2015)

tspan.tspan: Summary
: We design a system to allow for the communication between two users using
noninvasive neural recording and stimulation. EEG signals are decoded from one user, then
the result is encoded in the neural stimulation of another user through transcranial magnetic

text.tspan: stimulation, allowing them to complete a common goal.

tspan.tspan: Summary
: Neural networks trained on more than one task often suffer from catastrophic
forgetting. But how is the brain able to avoid this? We
find that learning a new task alters the
neural activity used to perform a familiar task, with
these alterations occurring along

text.tspan: dimensions output-null to the familiar task.

Convex Optimization for Calcium Imaging
DM Losey*, Y Chen*, A Rumack*

tspan.tspan: Summary
: We developed a model to infer neural activity from calcium imaging recordings,
using trend
filtering. To accomplish this, we created a Bayesian method to approximate integer programming.

text.tspan: We show that our method outperforms state-of-the-art in certain applications.
